ce:section.ce:para:
TGA technique was utilized to assess the thermal stability of ZnO-NPs@NCDs (
                           Fig. 14

                           ). Continuous loss in weight was measured in a range of 0–600 °C. The loss in weight between 30–120 °C was to the extent of 9.83 % and this loss was owing to the evaporation of water molecules bound on ZnO-NPs@NCDs. Between, 121–250 °C there was about 10.42 % loss which was associated to the decomposition of the hydroxyl/amine groups on the surface of ZnO-NPs@NCDs material. At 600 °C, there was about 75.65 % loss in weight and it could be due to the breakdown of oxygen containing functional moieties and carbon construction along with subsequent liberation of CO2. Thus, total loss in weight from 30-600 °C was 96.6 % [60].
